  <p>When a log reaches Wazuh, it goes through four phases: <strong>pre-decoder</strong> (extracts the date and program), <strong>decoder</strong> (extracts fields with regex), <strong>rules</strong> (checks whether the event is relevant) and <strong>alert generation</strong> (if the rule matches, Wazuh notifies by email, Discord or Slack).</p>

  <h2>How do logs flow through Wazuh from entry to alert?</h2>

  <p>
    When a log enters Wazuh, it goes through several processing phases until it becomes an alert visible in the dashboard or sent by email/Discord/Slack. Understanding this flow is essential to create custom rules and configure effective alerts.
  </p>

